<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="63" type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="63">
<taxonomicName authority="Enderlein, 1912" authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1912" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Lichtwardtia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lichtwardtia ziczac" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ziczac">Lichtwardtia ziczac</taxonomicName>
(Wiedemann, 1824) sensu Zhang, Masunaga &amp; Yang, 2009: 199, figs 11-14. Re-description.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="63" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="63">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="63">
This species is dedicated to Dr. Lili Zhang of the IOZ Museum in Beijing who re-described and illustrated 
<taxonomicName authority="Enderlein, 1912" authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1912" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Lichtwardtia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lichtwardtia ziczac" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ziczac">Lichtwardtia ziczac</taxonomicName>
(Wiedemann) for the first time with detailed drawings.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="63" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="63">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="63">Costa without swelling. Hypandrium with a large brown dorsal preapical tooth. Phallus smooth.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="63" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="63">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="63">
For a full description we refer to 
<bibRefCitation author="Zhang, L" journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the American Entomological Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="63" pagination="197 - 203" title="Species of Lichtwardtia from China (Diptera: Dolichopodidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.3157/061.135.0208" volume="135" year="2009">Zhang et al. 2009</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="63" type="comments">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="63">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="63">
In having the cross veins clouded, 
<taxonomicName authority="Enderlein, 1912" authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1912" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Lichtwardtia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lichtwardtia ziczac" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ziczac">Lichtwardtia ziczac</taxonomicName>
(Wiedemann) is distinctly different from 
<taxonomicName genus="L." lsidName="L. ziczac" pageId="0" pageNumber="63" rank="species" species="ziczac">L. ziczac</taxonomicName>
sensu 
<bibRefCitation author="Zhang, L" journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the American Entomological Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="63" pagination="197 - 203" title="Species of Lichtwardtia from China (Diptera: Dolichopodidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.3157/061.135.0208" volume="135" year="2009">Zhang et al. 2009</bibRefCitation>
and therefore we give a new name 
<taxonomicName authority="Enderlein, 1912" authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1912" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Lichtwardtia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lichtwardtia zhangae" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zhangae">Lichtwardtia zhangae</taxonomicName>
sp. n. to the species that she (re-) described from Bali. It is very closely related to 
<taxonomicName genus="L." lsidName="L. polychroma" pageId="0" pageNumber="63" rank="species" species="polychroma">L. polychroma</taxonomicName>
from Sri Lanka and differs in the lacking of a swelling of the costa.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="63" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="63">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="63">Bali (Indonesia).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
